char.label: Inter-hemal spine cartilage of preural centrum 3, 4
Pseudotympanum present, most of hiatus located anterior to rib of fifth vertebra
Scales cycloid, very thin and deciduous
Lateral line incomplete, with 5(1), 6(n 7(7), 8(2) or 9*(3) perforated scales extending posteriorly to vertical through pelvic-fin origin
Dorsal-fin rays ii+8*(75), or rarely ii+9(2)
Anal-fin rays iii+19*(12), iii+20(19), iii+21(5) or iii+22(2)
Caudal-fin rays i+9+8+i*(29), dorsal procurrent rays 8(1), 9(3) or 10(7), ventral procurrent rays 7(2) or 8(9)
Caudal fin forked with both lobes of similar size

Male specimens (MZUSP 112114, 112116) with one to four hooks on the distal third of first four branched anal-fin rays, and one to five hooks along most of length of all pelvic-fin rays, except for medialmost ray
Heart shaped patch of dark chromatophores on dorsal portion of head from epiphyseal bar to tip of supraoccipital spine
Mesethmoid and anterior part of frontal distinctly sloped anteroventrally with anterior portion of neurocranium rounded in lateral view
Lateral wing of mesethmoid pointed distally and directed straight laterally
Lateral ethmoid present as a thin bony lamella, separated from frontal by remnants of lamina orbitonasalis cartilage
Nasal in form of bony tube
Frontal relatively long, forming most of lateral margin of anterior and posterior cranial fontanels, with supraorbital lateral-line canal running along its lateral margin
Epiphyseal branch of supraorbital canal short
Orbitosphenoid slender, separated from frontal by large elongate gap above its dorsal margin, with contact with frontal restricted to small areas anteriorly and posteriorly
Orbitosphenoid with conspicuous orbital process, i.e. median, slender horizontal process extending anteriorly towards rhinosphenoid and tapering posteriorly
Rhinosphenoid a small bone in cartilaginous orbital projection of trabecula communis
Pterosphenoid pierced by very large oval foramen sometimes present as two smaller foramina
Parasphenoid long and narrow, wider in its otic portion, with pair of short ascending processes near anteroventral margin of prootic
Prootic with large anterior foramen and even larger auditory foramen present on its ventral surface lateral to anterior saccular recess and covering approximately one-half of its ventral surface
Parietal short with small canal passing anteroposteriorly along its lateral portion not reaching contralateral canal
Sphenotic small but with relatively large sphenotic spine
Pterotic composed of both autopterotic and dermopterotic, with a small process on its ventral surface articulating with hyomandibular
Posterior spine-like process of pterotic absent
Epiotic restricted to ossification surrounding vertical semicircular canal and without lateral arm dividing posttemporal fossa, resulting in single large posttemporal fossa
Supraoccipital spine short, not extending above neural complex
Exoccipital well developed with large lateral occipital foramen forming approximately two-thirds of dorsal portion of lagenar capsule
Basioccipital relatively small, forming only approximately one-third of ventral portion of lagenar capsule and with Baudelot's ligament connecting anterior to capsule
Infraorbital 1 developed as weakly ossified tube
Infraorbitals 4 and 5 bony tubes with narrow posterior laminae
Thin band of scleral bone around distal perimeter of eye sclera, anterior area remaining cartilaginous
Premaxilla with series of four multicuspid teeth forming internal series and one conical external tooth
Dentary with single series of teeth extending along approximately anterior one-half of bone
Anguloarticular with small patch of cartilage medially representing remnant of coronoid process of Meckel's cartilage
Hyomandibular with large anterior flange of membrane bone
Metapterygoid with conspicuous horizontal crest dorsally and small vertical dorsomedial lamellar flange proximate to its articulation with endopterygoid
Quadrate-metapterygoid fenestra large and approximately round
Endopterygoid lamellar, ovoid and tapering anteriorly
Ectopterygoid lamellar, posteriorly tapering to pointed tip, and also becoming narrower anteriorly
Palatine present as small ossification in pars palatina of palatoquadrate cartilage
Anterior ceratohyal narrower along central portion
Claustrum poorly developed, present as small circular bone
Tripus well developed and robust with thick transformator process
Outer arm of os suspensorium robust and flattened, and inner arm projecting anteroventrally with expanded anterior tip meeting its counterpart in ventral midline
Baudelot's ligament consequently inserting anterior to lagenar capsule
Extrascapular present as inconspicuous vertical tubular bone anterior to posttemporal
Mesocoracoid well developed, rod-shaped and extending dorsally to anterior margin of cleithrum
Six distal radials less ossified, with three medial elements predominantly cartilaginous
Ischiatic process with small ventrally directed process
Parhypural with small flange of membrane bone on anterior margin
